Apache Stanbol Client is a tool that let Apache Stanbol integrators use it in an easy way. The only thing you need to do is to instantiate the client and run the Apache Stanbol operations. For example, you can do something like following:

StanbolClient sc = new StanbolClientImpl("http://localhost:8080/");
List<Enhancement> enhancements = sc.enhance(new File("/home/me/file.html"));
for(Enhancement enhancement : enhancements) {
    System.out.println("Created: " + enhancement.getCreated());
    System.out.println("Creator: " + enhancement.getCreator());

    if(enhancement instanceof EntityAnnotation) {
        EntityAnnotation annotation = (EntityAnnotation)enhancement;

        System.out.println("Entity label: " + annotation.getEntityLabel());
        System.out.println("Entity type: " + annotation.getEntityType());
        System.out.println("Entity reference: " + annotation.getEntityReference());
    } else if (enhancement instanceof TextAnnotation) {
        TextAnnotation annotation = (TextAnnotation)enhancement;
        
        System.out.println("Type: " + annotation.getType());
        System.out.println("Selected text: " + annotation.getSelectedText());
        System.out.println("Selection context: " + annotation.getSelectionContext());
    }

    System.out.println("Relation: " + enhancement.getRelation().size());
}


Apache Stanbol Client uses Jersey for the RestClient implementation and Openjenafor RDF parsing.
